Success Nwogu, Abuja The Chairman, Board of Trustees, Ijaw National Congress, Chief Edwin Clark, has urged the Governor of Bayelsa State, Senator Douye Diri, to work hard to earn the confidence and support of all Bayelsans and Ijaw. Clark, who is also Convener, Pan Niger Delta Forum, in a statement on Monday, also urged Diri to reach out individually to members of the Peoples Democratic Party who rightly or wrongly felt aggrieved and did not support his campaign efforts. He further advised him to have a good and personal working relationship with the candidate of the All Progressives Congress, Mr David Lyon. The former minister said, “I want you to pay close attention to making all humanly possible efforts to have a good and personal working relationship with your brother on the other side, Chief David Lyon of the All Progressives Congress and the leadership of his party. “I commend him for his spirit of sportsmanship in fully accepting the court verdict and asking all to support the Government as was shown in his statement of February 28, 2020. He has become a politician of weight in Bayelsa State who cannot be easily ignored. I expect both of you as leaders to work together in the overall interest of the state and the Ijaw nation. “I adjure you to pay very close attention to our struggle on the need to restructure Nigeria in line with the vision of the founding fathers. That is, a Nigeria with a robust federalist structures where there are no second-class citizens but where justice and equity reign.” Copyright PUNCH.
